President Donald J. Trump is [scheduled](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2026/02/17/trump-when-is-the-state-of-the-union-address/88726760007/) to deliver his State of the Union address on Feb. 24 starting at 9 p.m. ET.&#x20;

Last year at the time of his address to the joint session of Congress (technically it was not a SOTU since he was a new president), Trump [floated](https://www.whitehouse.gov/fact-sheets/2025/03/fact-sheet-president-donald-j-trump-establishes-the-strategic-bitcoin-reserve-and-u-s-digital-asset-stockpile/) the idea of a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve though did not mention it in his speech.

In November 2025 in his [remarks](https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/documents/remarks-the-american-business-forum-miami-florida) at the American Business Forum in Miami, Florida, Trump said:&#x20;

> We're making the United States the Bitcoin superpower, the crypto capital of the world, and the undisputed leader in artificial intelligence. We're leading China by a lot. And don't forget, if we don't do the crypto properly, China—China wants to do it. They're starting it, but they want to do it. Other countries want to do it. If we don't do it—it's a big industry.

